.help nfquick Feb2005 gemini.gnirs
.ih
NAME
.nf
nfquick -- Generate an acquisition image from IFU data
.fi
.ih
USAGE
nfquick image
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls image
Either a range specification for the file name indices (if \fIprefix\fR) is
also given), or a filename

See GEMLIST for more information on specifying input using the ranges.
.le
.ls prefix = ""
The date/instrument part of the file name (everything up to the
per-night index, typically ending in "S").
.le
.ls datadir = "/net/reggie/staging/perm/"
The directory in which the raw data are found.  This is preprended to
the file names generated using \fIroot\fR and \fIrange\fR.
.le
.ls outimages = ""
A list of output images.  The number of entries must match \fIinimages\fR
unless the parameter is empty (in which case \fIoutprefix\fR is used).
.le
.ls outprefix = "a"
The prefix used to generate output image names from the input image
list \fIinimages\fR if \fIoutimages\fR="".
.le
.ls mdf = "gnirs$data/gnirs-ifu-short-32-mdf2.fits
The MDF that describes the mapping from detector to sky.
.le
.ls shiftx, shifty = 0.0
The shifts to apply to the mapping in \fItable\fR (used if 
\fIfl_shift\fR=no).
.le
.ls xscale, yscale = 0.15
Arcsec/pixel for converting measurements for display.
.le
.ls dispaxis = 2
Dispersion axis (2 for GNIRS IFU)
.le
.ls fl_inter = yes
Measure shift interactively?
.le
.ls fl_compress = yes
Compress aperture to single row of pixels?
.le
.ls fl_display = yes
Display each image on stdimage?
.le
.ls raw_frame = 1
Frame to display raw data.
.le
.ls img_frame = 2
Frame to display reconstructed image data.
.le
.ls fl_shift = yes
Measure the shift to a central star in the image (used during acquisition).
.le
.ls logfile = ""
Name of logfile.  The GNIRS package logfile "gnirs.log" is used by default.
.le
.ls verbose = yes
Print more actions to the screen.
.le
.ls status = 0
Exit status will be non-zero if the procedure halted with an error.
This parameter is always set by the task, and should not be modified
by the user.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION
This task copies data from the IFU observations into new files, shifting
the data to create an approximation to sky observed.
.sp
The input parameters for specifying the input files work as for the
GEMLIST task.  This makes use during observing as simple as possible.
.sp
The task may work with other IFU data, but the output (instrument shifts
etc) is tailored to the GNIRS IFU.
.ih
EXAMPLE
1.  The basic usage is
.sp
.nf
  cl> nfquick 161
...
NFQUICK: press a or x to identify star and then q to quit
...
============================================================================
    GNIRS IFU instrument offsets (arcsec)  p=0.582  q=-1.680
============================================================================
 
                    Raw data source  S20041120S0161[1]
                Image size (pixels)  (35.000, 22.000)
         Standard location (pixels)  (17.500, 10.500)
             Measured peak (pixels)  (28.700, 14.380)
                    Offset (pixels)  (11.200, 3.880 )
                    Offset (arcsec)  (1.680 , 0.582 )
.fi
.ih
